# shadcn UI only

- **Use exclusively shadcn components** from `@/components/ui` for all UI (buttons, inputs, cards, forms, dialogs, etc.). Do not use raw HTML elements for UI that shadcn provides.
- **Add new components** with: `pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add <component-name> --yes` when a primitive is missing. Prefer existing shadcn primitives over custom implementations.
- **Follow shadcn patterns**: use the `cn()` utility from `@/lib/utils` for class merging; respect the design tokens in `globals.css` (e.g. `primary`, `muted`, `card`); use the variants and sizes defined by each component (e.g. `Button` variants: default, outline, ghost, link).
- **Styling**: rely on Tailwind classes that map to the theme (e.g. `bg-primary`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-border`). Do not introduce arbitrary colors or one-off styles that bypass the design system.
- **Composition**: build complex UIs by composing shadcn components (Card, CardHeader, CardContent, etc.) rather than custom div-based layouts for interactive pieces.
